<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vilem</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Anyone makin a Window program for DAoC, or knows where to get one??</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">J3K</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It'd be nice to find one.  IMO it's the top priority.  There's many people out there who can't afford to dedicate 100% of their system to a game 100% of the time while playing.  (Me being one of those people, which is why I canceled and dont play anymore.  I just cant afford to stare at a game for more than 5 minutes without -something- needing my attention)<P>....<P>although, come to think about it, I'm wondering how it'd work.  For an app to work nicely windowed in D3D8 it'd need to be created as a window, which means that the exclusive flags can stay but the windowed flags would have to change.  I'm trying to think how that could be done without actually editing the EXE itself.  Would have to cook up a custom D3D interface, perhaps (Its been done).  <P>Once easy windowed-mode is in, it should be a lot easier to make it so it doesnt know its been alt-tabbed.  And in windowed mode its far less likely to lose its textures.<p>[This message has been edited by J3K (edited 12-03-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerry</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Consider this: while Odin's Eye is a Linux program it is probable that Mythic won't lose too much sleep over it.  But the minute any kind of Windows port comes out, they are probably going to be all over this place.  You can expect constant shuffling of the packet protocol, which means an endless arms race for Slicer.<P>This is basically what happened with ShowEQ as well as I can remember.  Verant didn't give seem to give a shit until a windows version came out.<p>[This message has been edited by Jerry (edited 12-03-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">gathalian</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">yea.. probably a window version would not work...  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/frown.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Scuffed</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I think he meant a program to run DAOC in windowed mode, not a windows version of Odin's Eye.....</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">J3K</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, I meant being able to run DAoC in a window, or to at least alt tab out of it.  I've been thinking about it, and I'm thinking along more generalized route, er, I mean something which allows DirectX to render to a window as if it were full screen.  <BR>All solutions would have to work without actually touching camelot files</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">gathalian</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Diablo 2 runs on full screen.. and can alt-tab.. but have you try running in window mode.. it is a bit slow (1.6ghtz with 512 meg of ram and 64 meg geoforce2 vid card) also use directX.. so might not run as smooth in full screen.. would be nice. .then you can ICQ,IM or email.. or look up map via the web while you are working on your tradeskill or running from location to location or horse back riding (what else to do during a long ride?)<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tex</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">[]D [] []V[] []D</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vilem</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yah, thats true that Diablo II runs slower in window mode, but, EverQuest runs perfectly in its window mode, EQW, so it actually might be possible to run DAoC at full speed.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Noisy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The program that was out a couple weeks ago worked great, but they updated and down it went.  <IMG SRC="http://www.ethernalquest.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>=n=</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vilem</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yea, i know that, but I think, JSD is making a 3.0 that will work with the DX8.dll.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
